    <sec>
      <title>Performance evaluation</title>
      <p>We compared the predictions from PlantTFcat with the benchmark data in PlnTFDB [<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="B7">7</xref>] using the <italic>Arabidopsis thaliana</italic> genome release V8 (TAIR8) and the <italic>Zea mays</italic> genome release 3b.50 (<ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="http://www.maizesequence.org/">http://www.maizesequence.org/</ext-link>). PlantTFcat missed 199 genes out of 2,757 TF/TR gene models from the <italic>Arabidopsis thaliana</italic> data in PlnTFDB. Moreover, PlantTFcat reported 1,744 additional gene models as TF/TR/CR candidates. Of these identified gene models, only 95 were not confirmed, because they were annotated as either unknown or non-TF/TR genes per the TAIR8 annotation (see Additional file <xref ref-type="supplementary-material" rid="S2">2</xref>). In the monocot species, <italic>Zea mays</italic>, PlantTFcat achieves a similar prediction performance: 370 genes were missed and 6,050 genes were newly predicted as TF/TR/CR genes (see Additional file <xref ref-type="supplementary-material" rid="S3">3</xref>) (TableÂ <xref ref-type="table" rid="T1">1</xref>). Such results suggest that PlantTFcat can predict TF/TR/CR genes with high coverage and sensitivity.</p>
